t: A Song of degrees for Solomon.
Except*p the Lord*s build the house, they labour in vain that build it: except the Lord*s keep the city, the watchman waketh but in vain.
It*p is vain for you to rise up early, to sit up late, to eat the bread of sorrows: for so he giveth his beloved sleep.
Lo,*p children are an heritage of the Lord:*s and the fruit of the womb is his reward.
As*p arrows are in the hand of a mighty man; so are children of the youth.
Happy*p is the man that hath his quiver full of them: they shall not be ashamed, but they shall speak with the enemies in the gate.
